    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "The narrator's father witnessed Ali ibn Abi Talib (peace be upon him) passing by a group that included Salman al-Farsi. Upon seeing Ali, Salman urged the group to 'be attached to this man,' swearing by God that no one besides Ali could inform them of the intimate secrets of their Prophet. This hadith highlights Salman's recognition of Ali's unique knowledge and authority.",
